list.abstract: depend（英[dɪˈpend]，美[dɪˈpend]），英语单词，动词，意思为信赖‘’视…而定；决定于。短语搭配有depend on（取决于；依赖, 依靠），例句为“They depend on adequate sleep to thrive.（他们依靠充足的睡眠来茁壮成长。）” depend不及物动词类近义词有hope、tie to，名词形式为dependence、dependability。
《Depend》是Birdman、Jacquees、King Issa、FYB演唱的一首歌曲，收录于2018年11月16日发行的专辑《Lost At Sea 2 (Explicit)》中。

yingyinNormal.en: David's story is disturbing to me. If the bees are in trouble, so are the farmers who depend on them and the consumers who want fresh produce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大卫的故事对我影响很大，要是蜜蜂正在危险之中,那么那些依赖他们的农民，那些想吃新鲜水果的消费者。

yingyinNormal.en: All these flights depend on Debra's ability to manage America's airspace. She's good at it, and the system works well, most of the time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所有的这些飞机都依赖于黛布拉对美国空域的管理能力，她精通这个系统，并且运转的很好，尤其是在时间方面。

yingyinNormal.en: And you have to listen to me. You're very lives depend on it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们一定要听我说这对你们来说很重要。

yingyinNormal.en: All right. How does the flow rate in a pipe depend on its diameter?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，管直径如何决定流量。

yingyinNormal.en: Because I can depend on him, Because he's the most loyal person I've ever met,
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为我可以信赖他，他是我见过的最忠诚的人。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't know, it would totally depend on her coloring and you got the job. Yes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那完全要看她的肤色，而定你拿到那工作了！

yingyinNormal.en: All of these depend on the other branches, which keeps executive power in check.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些都要靠其他机构保证行政权受控。

yingyinNormal.en: Let's work together. We'll find them. The course of human history may depend on it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 让我们一起努力找到他们吧，改写人类的历史， 就完全寄托在他们身上了。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, believe it or not, the fate of the entire damn human race might depend on it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，不管你信不信，整个人类的命运可全靠它了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it would depend who it was, of course. Would it? That's interesting. Of course it would.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个当然要取决于和谁结婚。是吗? 有意思，当然是了。

yingyinNormal.en: So our lives are just gonna depend on whatever nature decides to do with us? Or what we do with our human nature.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以我们的生活是什么样子只能取决于自然决定我们是什么样子，或者取决于我们怎么对待人性。

yingyinNormal.en: You don't have to use a silver bullet. But if you forge one, well, then we don't have to depend upon the kindness of monsters.
yingyinNormal.zh: 并不是非得使用银子弹，但如果造一颗出来，那么，我们就不必再仰仗怪物们的怜悯了。

yingyinNormal.en: And, if you can't, you need to find any means possible to drop cover and hold on. Because your life is gonna depend on it. God be with you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如若来不及的话，你们需要找到任何何以掩护或者抓牢的东西。因为你们能不能活下来全靠它了。愿上帝与你们同在。

examination_example.sentence: It's not necessarily a bad thing, but <highlight>depending</highlight> on the school, it can be costly to make up credits after switching too late in the game.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这不一定是坏事，但要视学校而定，太晚换专业的话，要补学分得花很多钱。

examination_example.sentence: How we read a given text also <highlight>depends</highlight> to some extent on our particular interest in reading it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们如何阅读给定的文本，在某种程度上，也取决于我们对阅读它的特殊兴趣。

examination_example.sentence: In theory, the success of an applicant should not <highlight>depend</highlight> on the few others chosen randomly for interview during the same day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从理论上讲，应聘者的成功不应该取决于当天随机挑选的其他几位面试者。

examination_example.sentence: You work with them every day, and you <highlight>depend</highlight> on them just as they <highlight>depend</highlight> on you.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你每天和他们一起工作，你依赖他们，就像他们依赖你一样。

examination_example.sentence: Immersive reading, by contrast, <highlight>depends</highlight> on being willing to risk inefficiency, godlessness, even time-wasting.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，沉浸式阅读依赖于愿意冒效率低下、无神甚至浪费时间的风险。

examination_example.sentence: Everyone makes fun of it, but managers love it, companies <highlight>depend</highlight> on it, and regular people willingly absorb it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人人都调侃它，但经理们却热衷于它，企业也依靠它，普通人也乐意学习并接受它。

word_usage.usage:
depend on和rely on都表示“依靠”，区别在于：
depend on sb./sth.强调很可能从这个人或这件事中得到支持或帮助。
rely on sb./sth.强调凭以往的经验来判断是否可以相信或依赖。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 专指由于自身能力不足或缺乏自信心而依赖别人给予帮助或支持，同时主观认为这种依赖不会遭到拒绝。
一般指根据以往的经验而指望某人不会辜负希望或期待某事不落空。
